  "No, the fog is actually liquid carbon dioxide dripping off the dry ice and pooling": "",
  "The white fog is not CO2 gas — carbon dioxide is invisible. The fog consists of tiny water droplets that form when the extremely cold CO2 gas chills the surrounding moist air.": "",
